      "created": "2018-11-01T05:06:30.983+0000",
      "description": "Delay scheduling was introduced to honor task locality at best-effort, which has node/rack level delays. However under cloud environment, usually the storage is remote to the work-load cluster, which makes the locality constraint totally irrelevant. Lets revisit this and create a model for cloud environments without too many setups.",
